quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  43,68,"[It will be said to them], “O My slaves, there is no fear for you Today, nor will you grieve"
  43,69,"[those] who believed in Our verses and submitted [to Us as Muslims]"
  43,70,"Enter Paradise, you and your spouses, rejoicing in bliss.”"
  43,71,"Golden trays and cups will be passed around among them; there will be all that souls desire and eyes delight in, and you will abide therein forever"
  43,72,That is Paradise which you will inherit for what you used to do
  43,73,You will have therein abundant fruit to eat from
  43,74,"Indeed, the wicked will be in the punishment of Hell forever"
  43,75,"It will not be lightened for them, and they will remain therein in utter despair"
  43,76,"We did not wrong them, but they themselves were the wrongdoers"
  43,77,"They will cry out, “O Mālik, let your Lord put an end to us!” He will say, “You are here to stay.”"
  43,78,"We surely brought you the truth, but most of you were averse to the truth"
  43,79,Have they devised a plan? We too have devised a plan
  43,80,"Do they think that We do not hear their secret talks and private counsels? Yes indeed, and Our angel-messengers are with them recording everything"
  43,81,"Say, “If the Most Compassionate truly had a son, I would be the first of [his] worshipers.”"
  43,82,"Glory be to the Lord of the heavens and earth, Lord of the Throne, far above what they ascribe [to Him]"
  43,83,So leave them to indulge in falsehood and amuse themselves until they meet their Day that they are promised
  43,84,"It is He Who is God in the heaven and God on earth, and He is the All-Wise, the All-Knowing"
  43,85,"Blessed is He to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and earth and all that is between them. With Him is the knowledge of the Hour, and to Him you will be returned"
  43,86,"Those whom they supplicate besides Him have no power to intercede, except those who testify to the truth on the basis of knowledge"
  43,87,"If you ask them who created them, they will surely say, “Allah.” How are they then deluded"
  43,88,"[The Prophet] said: “O my Lord, indeed, these are a people who do not believe.”"
  43,89,"So turn away from them and say, “Peace.” They will come to know"